In England, in the seven days to 15 October, there were 253,269 new confirmed cases (447.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 October, there were 207,896 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 22% (45,373 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 October is 7,303,864 (12,915.7 cases per 100,000 population).
